com.nokia.sm.net
Interface SnapEventListener

public interface SnapEventListener

Callback interface for asynchronous SNAP Mobile event notification. This interface is used by the ServerComm class to notify registered listeners of received events and errors. Listeners need to implement this interface to be able to register themselves.

ServerComm instance calls into client code happen synchronously. This means that the calling ServerComm instance thread is blocked while the client method executes. Client code for the notification methods below needs to complete quickly in order to avoid stalling ServerComm instances.

See Also:
ServerComm.addSnapEventListener(com.nokia.sm.net.SnapEventListener), ServerComm.retrieveEvents(int, int, int), ServerComm.retrieveAllEvents()

Method Detail

processEvents

void processEvents(java.util.Vector list)
Instances of the ServerComm class will call this method for registered listeners each time new events are available. The listener is passed a Vector containing one or more ItemList instances. Each of these instances has an integer field named id which identifies the type of the event.

Parameters:
list - A list of Snap Mobile events. Each element is an ItemList instance.
See Also:
ItemList

processServerError

void processServerError(int code,
                        java.lang.String message,
                        int severity)
Instances of the ServerComm class will call this method for registered listeners each time the server returns an error. The client code then needs to take the appropriate action based on the severity of the error.

Parameters:
code - The numeric error code.
message - The textual message for the error.
severity - The severity of the error.
